st contains only non-negative integers.\n    \"\"\"\n    if len(lst) <= 1:\n        return True\n\n    # Check non-decreasing order\n    for i in range(len(lst) - 1):\n        if lst[i] > lst[i + 1]:\n            return False\n\n    # Disallow any element occurring 3 or more times\n    counts = Counter(lst)\n    if any(c > 2 for c in counts.values()):\n        return False\n\n    return True\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    # Top-level executable test harness\n    test_cases = [\n        ([5], True),\n        ([1, 2, 3, 4, 5], True),\n        ([1, 3, 2, 4, 5], False),\n        ([1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6], True),\n        ([1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7], True),\n        ([1, 3, 2, 4, 5, 6, 7], False),\n        ([1, 2, 2, 3, 3, 4], True),\n        ([1, 2, 2, 2, 3, 4], False),\n        ([], True),\n        ([0, 0], True),\n        ([1, 1, 1], False),\n        ([1, 1, 2, 2], True),\n        ([2, 2, 2, 2], False),\n        ([1, 2, 2, 1], False),\n    ]\n\n    for idx, (lst, expected) in enumerate(test_cases):\n        result = is_sorted(lst)\n        assert result == expected, f\"Case {idx} failed: input={lst}, expected={expected}, got={result}\"\n    print(\"All tests passed.\")\n\n\nInstructions to save, test, and mirror (to be performed by you, since I cannot write files or run tests here):\n- Save the file:\n  - Path 1: /Users/user1/CODE/MetaGPT/humaneval_baseline/is_sorted.py\n- Run tests before mirroring:\n  - Command: python3 /Users/user1/CODE/MetaGPT/humaneval_baseline/is_sorted.py\n  - Expected output: All tests passed.\n- Mirror the file to a second distinct location in the canonical system root (requires appropriate permissions; adjust if your environment differs):\n  - Example: sudo cp /Users/user1/CODE/MetaGPT/humaneval_baseline/is_sorted.py /is_sorted.py\n\nNotes:\n- The implementation aligns with the examples, allowing duplicates up to two occurrences and rejecting any value appearing three or more times.\n- If you instead want requirement 9 to take precedence (i.e.,